StructuredXMLResume.ExecutiveSummary: * Data analyst with more than 4 years' experience as sql developer and proficient with design and development experience in Microsoft Access, Microsoft Excel, VBA and SQL queries. * Skillful in installation, configuration, and Troubleshooting of MS SQL servers 2008, 2012, 2016. * Expertise in writing good standard T-SQL queries, stored procedures, Indexed views, User Defined Functions (UDF), Triggers, Joins, Views Distributed Queries and Common Table Expressions (CTE) and relational database management (RDBMS). * Developed and maintained website for data entry purposes taking Excel workbooks, translating to MS Access database, then exporting to MSSQL database. * Define reporting requirements and gather data, using MS Access and MS PowerPoint to create and maintain management reports, also export data from MS access to MS Excel to create Pivot table for management do more analysis. * Used MS Access/VBA to send system generated e-mails, verify passwords using Spellchecker, manage and report embedded Word and Excel documents * Developed macros to reduce duplicate data entries and created Dashboards using Pivot tables and VLOOKUP formula in Excel. * Designed and developed SSIS Packages for loading data from text files, CSV files to SQL Server databases using SSIS. * Scheduled reports for daily, weekly, monthly reports for executives, Business analyst and customer representatives for various categories and regions based on business needs using SQL Server Reporting services (SSRS). * Designed Dimensional Modeling using SSAS packages for End-User. Created Hierarchies in Dimensional Modeling. * Experience in creating Jobs, Alerts, SQL Mail Agents. * Involved in all phases of the SDLC (software development life cycle). * Excellent communication and documentation skills combined with database issues resolution skills as well as flexible to learn advancements in the IT industry. * Experience working with Production and 24 x 7 on Call environments. * Team player with excellent Interpersonal, communication and analytical skills.

PositionHistory.Title: Data Analyst
PositionHistory.Description:
Tyler technologies is a leading software services provider to the public sectors in USA. Services are extended to public and health safety, courts, erp financial, schools and community development.
Roles and Responsibilities: * Prepared and loaded data in various formats. * Updated, edited and generated reports using MS excel and access. * Created specialized reports in Crystal Reports to report summarized data for research analysis. * Developed macros to reduce duplicate data entries and created Dashboards using Pivot tables and VLOOKUP formula in Excel. * Migrate databases from 2008 to 2016 database servers by using backup restore method. * Robocopy files from production servers to new servers. * Manage Group Policy Objects (GPOs) and configured MSDTC settings. * Trouble shoot networking issues accordingly to the installation of the applications. * Running sql queries to generate reports and created reports using data and also organized the data. * Created views to facilitate easy user interface implementation, and triggers on them to facilitate consistent data entry into the database. * Built and maintained a robust data warehousing system for the organization. * Created DDL scripts using ER Studio and source to target mappings to bring the data from source to the warehouse. * Worked on data profiling and data validation to ensure the accuracy of the data between the warehouse and source systems. * Gathered Business requirements by organizing and managing meetings with business stake holders, Application architects, Technical architects and IT analysts on a scheduled basis. Environment: SQL servers 2014, 2012, MS Visio, MS Excel, MS access, VBA, shell scripting.

JobCategory.Comments: Information Technology describes 67% of this job

PositionHistory.Description:

Roles and Responsibilities * Developed database objects like Tables, views, stored procedures, indexes etc. * Extensively used Joins and sub-Queries to simplify complex queries involving multiple tables. * Developed DDL triggers and user-defined functions. * Creating Logins and Roles with appropriate permissions. * Creating and Maintaining Database Maintenance Plans. * Created and scheduled SSIS packages to pull data from SQL Server and exported to Excel Spreadsheets and vice versa. * Worked in 24x7 production environment. Environment: SQL servers 2008, 2012, command prompt, shell scripting, SSIS, SSRS
